<HEADLINE>
IC INDUSTRY'S PRODUCTION VALUE TO HIT NT$1.55 TRILLION FOR 2007
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, March 7 (CNA) 03/07/07  14:47:11 (By Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
The production value of Taiwan's integrated circuits (IC)
industry amounted to NT$1.39 trillion (US$42.1 billion) for 2006,
marking an increase of 24.6 percent over the year-earlier figure,
according to tallies released Wednesday by the Industrial
Economics and Knowledge Center (IEK) of the Hsinchu-based
Industrial Technology Research Institute.
</P>
<P>
The IEK predicted that IC industry's production value will
increase by 11.5 percent to reach NT$1.55 billion for 2007.
</P>
<P>
According to the IEK statistics, IC testing businesses generated
a production value of NT$92.4 trillion last year, for annual
growth of 36.9 percent -- the best performance among all relevant
IC businesses.
</P>
<P>
The IC manufacturing sector's production value reached NT766.7
billion for 2006, registering annual growth of 30.5 percent,
while that of the IC package sector amounted to NT$210.8 billion,
for growth of 18.4 percent, and that of the IC design sector hit
NT$323.4 billion, for growth of 13.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The IC testing sector is expected to generate production value of
NT$102.9 billion this year, for annual growth of 11.4 percent,
while the 2007 production value of the package sector is expected
to increase to NT$245.9 billion for growth of 16.7 percent, that
of the design sector is forecast to rise to NT$369.9 billion for
growth of 14.3 percent, and that of the manufacturing sector is
forecast to hit NT$835 billion for growth of 8.9 percent,
according to the IEK.
</P>
